<h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="details-title">Details</h2>


<div aria-labelledby="details-title">
  
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<div class="call-to-action">
<h4 id="stay-up-to-date">Stay up to date</h4>

<p>This page tells you what to do if there’s a no-deal Brexit. It will be updated if anything changes, including if a deal is agreed.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/email-signup/?topic=/government/brexit">Sign up for email alerts</a> to get the latest information.</p>
</div>

<p>This spreadsheet sets out the ‘on hold’ health claims that may continue to be used in the UK if there’s a no-deal Brexit.</p>

<p>The claims may be used subject to the conditions set out in the following guidance:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/changes-to-nutrition-legislation-if-theres-no-eu-exit-deal">The Nutrition (Amendment etc.) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019: practical changes for industry</a></li>
  <li>
<a rel="external" href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/307453/DH_BULLETIN_-_Searching_Article_13.1_on_hold_health_claims_acc.pdf">Guidance bulletin: Article 13(1) ‘on hold’ health claims spreadsheet</a> (published 2014)</li>
</ul>

</div>
</div>

</div>

